result.reason: Root cause is 32-bit address space exhaustion (~1GB limit with RDP v8+ ActiveX); already resolved by native x64 builds shipped since v1.80.0
result.approach: No code changes needed — x64 builds (.NET 10 migration) remove the 32-bit memory ceiling. Users should use x64 build for 50+ simultaneous RDP connections.

attempts.raw_output:
Based on the issue details and comments, this is a 32-bit virtual address space limitation with the RDP ActiveX control (mstscax.dll). Each RDP v8+ connection consumes significant memory, hitting the ~1GB/2GB ceiling after 15-20 connections. The fork already ships native x64 builds (.NET 10) which eliminates this constraint.
